<hl>
<seg id=1> China becomes a leading country in the production and exporting of Feather Plumes. </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> Xinhua News agency, Beijing, September 1st, by Niang Zhou- The Chinese Feather and  Plume Industry has been growing for more than ten years, and has become an important element in Chinese light industry.  The volume and value of annual exports accounts for half of the total amount of the feather and plume trade in the world, and has gained a good reputation from the International feather market </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=3> Chinese Feather and Plume industry started to develop rapidly since the middle of the 80's.  The whole industry took advantage of Chinese resources and human resources and imported advanced technology and equipment from overseas.  The quantity and quality of the product has been increased on a large scale. </seg>
<seg id=4> According to incomplete statistics, currently there are more than 3000 Feather and Plume manufacturing enterprises, among them, more than 600 have reached a certain standard with more than 300,000 employees.  Forming production capabilities exceeding 50,000,000 pieces annually.  The annual gross Industry product is valued at 800,000,000 Yuan. </seg>
<seg id=5> After more than ten years of market development, China has become the Leading country in the world in the production of feathers and plumes.  Annual export of feathers and plumes approach 30,000 tons.  Production of things made from feathers and plumes is more than 20,000,000 pieces.  The amount of foreign exchange approaches 82,000,000 US dollars, of which feathered and plumed clothing accounts for 50% of the total value of exports. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=6> It is presented that the quality of Chinese Feather and Plume production has been gradually improved. </seg>
<seg id=7> In the last half-year, the government conducted random quality inspections in 56 feather and plume clothing enterprises.  The products of 47 enterprises passed the inspection, accounting for 84%. </seg>
<seg id=8> In the competitive market, the brand names of these products have become famous and gained a good reputation, such as Jiangxi's yaya, Beijing's yilinan, Guangdong's genanchi, Shichuan's tiange. </seg>
</p>
